# =============================================================================
# Frontbase Distributed Cloud — Environment Router
# =============================================================================
# This directory holds FOUR independent tiers, each deployed as its own
# compose service (usually on separate machines):
#
#   docker-compose.api-tier.yml     -> use .env.api-tier.example
#   docker-compose.core-tier.yml    -> use .env.core-tier.example
#   docker-compose.data-tier.yml    -> use .env.data-tier.example
#   docker-compose.static-tier.yml  -> use .env.static-tier.example
#
# Panels (EasyPanel etc.) auto-load only THIS file into their Environment
# editor. Replace this content with the matching tier example above, fill in
# the values, and keep "Create .env file" enabled — compose reads the panel's
# .env from this directory for ${VAR} interpolation, and each tier compose
# also accepts an optional .env.<tier> file for the CLI workflow.
#
# CLI workflow instead:
#   cp .env.api-tier.example .env.api-tier
#   docker compose -f docker-compose.api-tier.yml --env-file .env.api-tier up -d
# =============================================================================
